'''''Ever a Hero Be''''' was a ballad penned by [[Thalloviir Vaundruth]], [[Bard]] of [[Beregost]], in [[1344 DR]].

{{quote|''...But deep in halls dark and haunted<br/>Even heroes bold, high-vaunted<br/>Twice and thrice, to end up daunted<br/>Think of loved ones deeply wanted<br/>And much safer places to be...''}}
